# UI Components Guide

Authoritative index of reusable components and when to use them.

## Layout

- **Page** — full-screen route scaffold with paddings.
  - Use for top-level views.
  - File: [Page.vue](mdc:packages/design-system/src/components/Page.vue)
- **Section** — logical grouping inside a page.
  - Use to separate major areas, with title/description.
  - File: [Section.vue](mdc:packages/design-system/src/components/Section.vue)
- **Card** — elevated or bordered container for content blocks.
  - Use for contained modules and dashboards.
  - File: [Card.vue](mdc:packages/design-system/src/components/Card.vue)
- **HStack/VStack** — horizontal/vertical layout primitives.
  - Use for simple spacing and alignment.
  - Files: [HStack.vue](mdc:packages/design-system/src/components/HStack.vue), [VStack.vue](mdc:packages/design-system/src/components/VStack.vue)
- **Form** — opinionated form layout.
  - Use for grouped fields with consistent spacing.
  - File: [Form.vue](mdc:packages/design-system/src/components/Form.vue)

