## Navigation

- **Header** — top app bar with title and actions.
  - File: [Header.vue](mdc:packages/design-system/src/components/Header.vue)
- **BottomNav** — primary tab navigation.
  - File: [BottomNav.vue](mdc:apps/dollarwise/src/components/ui/navigation/BottomNav.vue)
- **Link** — unified link component for internal (Vue Router) and external URLs.
  - Auto-detects external links (http://, mailto:, tel:, etc.)
  - Supports `newTab`, `disabled`, `replace`, and `custom` slot rendering
  - Use instead of `<a>` or `router.push()` for clickable navigation
  - File: [Link.vue](mdc:packages/design-system/src/components/Link.vue)
  - Types: [Link.types.ts](mdc:packages/design-system/src/components/Link.types.ts)

## When to Use What (Decision Hints)

- Need a new screen? Start with `Page` → compose `Section`/`Card`.
- Listing entities? Use `List` + `ListItem`; put avatars/icons in the left slot.
- Collecting amounts? Use `CurrencyField`; free text → `TextField`.
- No data to show? Use `Empty` with a clear call to action `Button`.
- Navigating to another page/route? Use `Link` for proper accessibility; use `custom` slot for styled buttons that navigate.

